ucturing and legal advisory experience from  to  he was a founding partner and senior principal at apollo global management llc and lion advisors mr cogut cofounded and was one of the original partners and senior principal at apollo advisors lp a position he held for five years he was involved in all aspects of apollo’s distressed securities investments and restructuring activities and was the principal transaction architect and chief negotiator in the acquisition of the insurance business and high yield bond portfolio of executive life for consideration in excess of  billion from  to  he was a consultant and advisor principally to drexel burnham lambert incorporated and associated entities from  to  he practiced law at irell  manella in los angeles he also cofounded polyphony he has been the chairman of lighting science group corporation since february   and as its director since december   he serves as the chairman of re community holdings lp he serves as the chairman of the external advisory board of the brown universityveterans administration center for restorative and regenerative medicine mr cogut serves as chairman of the polyphony foundation he served as chairman at recommunity recycling llc mr cogut is a member of the executive council of the clinton health access initiative and serves as the chairman of the cogut center for the humanities at brown university he serves as a member of the advisory board of simon equity llc he serves as a director of mph energy midco lp human rights first the gettysburg foundation the clean economy development center and the r regions of climate action he also serves as a trustee of brown university he serves on the board of arizona state university’s global institute of sustainability he served as a director of perry ellis menswear llc salant corporation vail resorts inc and envirotest systems corporation mr cogut served as the chairman of fcr llc he served as a director at re community holdings ii inc he served as a director at max rave llc since august  mr cogut is an active philanthropist in the fields of improving education building civil society and championing environmental and health issues in  mr cogut was selected to win the new york league of conservation voters corporate pioneer award he is a graduate of harvard law school and brown universityread full background corporate headquarters  river roadcos cob connecticut united statesphone fax  board members memberships president founder chief executive officer managing partner and chairmanpegasus capital advisors lpchairmanre community holdings lpdirectormph energy midco lppresentchairmanlighting science group corporation education unknownother education brown universityunknownother education harvard law school other affiliations apollo global management llcenvirotest systems corpfcr llcperry ellis menswear llcvail resorts incmax rave llcpegasus partners ii lppegasus partners iii lpbrown universityharvard law schoolrecommunity recycling llcpegasus partners iv lpsimon equity llclighting science group corporationpegasus partners v lpre community holdings lprecommunity holdings ii incmph energy midco lp annual compensation there is no annual compensation data available stocks options there is no stock options data available total compensation there is no total compensation data available request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global bloombergcom does not create or control the content for inquiries please contact sp global market intelligence directly by clicking here stock quotes market data is delayed at least  minutes company lookup competitor compensationthere is no competitor compensation data available sponsored financial commentaries sponsored links browse companies a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z              request profile update only a company representative may request an update for the compa